									Tomas Fuentes on October 21, 2017
									                                

                                
									Reply ↓                                


                            I have to put images on my dice.
What is your opinion on heat transferred dice vs hard stamp (don’t know the term when an image is embedded)
and thank you so much on all the advice you’ve given, I really appreciate it.

                        
                    
                    


                
                
                        
                        
							
                        
                    
                    
                    
                        
                            
									James Mathe on October 22, 2017
									                                

                                
									Reply ↓                                


                            Dice are either heat transferred, silk screened, laser etched, or made from a mold. The first two will wear off after regular use and I don’t recommend them unless you 100% need full color or are stuck having to use the cheapest option possible. The laser makes sense if your details are too sharp for a mold or you only need a small quantity of dice overall (like 1000 or less), but if that’s not the case it’s best to use a mold.  Hope that helps. Please ask questions not directly related to my blog post in our FACEBOOK forums. https://www.facebook.com/groups/TabletopPublishers/

                        
                    
                    


                

	
